nstrates that if we actively engage with the governments and businesses building the internet of things, we have a chance to build a new kind of internet—and a more open society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aElectronic surveillance. 0aInformation technologyxPolitical aspects. 0aInternetxSocial aspects. 0aPrivacy, Right of. 0aTechnological innovationsxPolitical aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021366940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300213669423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300213669/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles